---
import DocLayout from '../../layouts/DocLayout.astro';
import PropsTable from '../../components/PropsTable.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../components/CodeBlock.astro';
import StorybookPreview from '../../components/StorybookPreview.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL || '/storyhouse-design-system/';
const currentPath = `${base}components/chip`;
---

<DocLayout
  title="Chip"
  status="stable"
  description="Compact label components for tags, statuses, filters, and categories. Supports variants, icons, dots, and removable chips."
  currentPath={currentPath}
>
  <section>
    <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
    <p>
      The <code>Chip</code> component displays compact pieces of information such as tags, status indicators,
      or filter values. It comes in six visual variants, two sizes, and supports optional icons, dot indicators,
      removal buttons, and interactive (clickable) behavior.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="variants">Variants</h2>
    <p>Chip supports six visual variants for different contexts.</p>

    <div class="my-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm dark:border-gray-800 dark:bg-gray-900">
      <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-gray-100 px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 dark:bg-gray-800 dark:text-gray-300">Default</span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-blue-100 px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium text-blue-700 dark:bg-blue-900 dark:text-blue-300">Primary</span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-green-100 px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium text-green-700 dark:bg-green-900 dark:text-green-300">Success</span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-yellow-100 px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium text-yellow-700 dark:bg-yellow-900 dark:text-yellow-300">Warning</span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-red-100 px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium text-red-700 dark:bg-red-900 dark:text-red-300">Danger</span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full border border-gray-300 bg-white px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 dark:border-gray-600 dark:bg-transparent dark:text-gray-300">Outline</span>
    </div>

    <CodeBlock title="chip-variants.tsx" code={`import { Chip } from '@storyhouse/components';

export function ChipVariants() {
  return (
    <div className="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
      <Chip variant="default">Default</Chip>
      <Chip variant="primary">Primary</Chip>
      <Chip variant="success">Success</Chip>
      <Chip variant="warning">Warning</Chip>
      <Chip variant="danger">Danger</Chip>
      <Chip variant="outline">Outline</Chip>
    </div>
  );
}`} />
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="features">Features</h2>

    <h3>Dot Indicator</h3>
    <p>Add a colored dot before the label using the <code>dot</code> prop, useful for status indicators.</p>

    <div class="my-4 flex flex-wrap gap-3 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm dark:border-gray-800 dark:bg-gray-900">
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 rounded-full bg-green-100 px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium text-green-700 dark:bg-green-900 dark:text-green-300">
        <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-green-500"></span>Online
      </span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 rounded-full bg-yellow-100 px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium text-yellow-700 dark:bg-yellow-900 dark:text-yellow-300">
        <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-yellow-500"></span>Away
      </span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 rounded-full bg-red-100 px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium text-red-700 dark:bg-red-900 dark:text-red-300">
        <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-red-500"></span>Offline
      </span>
    </div>

    <h3>Removable</h3>
    <p>Set <code>removable</code> to show an X button that fires <code>onRemove</code> when clicked.</p>

    <div class="my-4 flex flex-wrap gap-3 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm dark:border-gray-800 dark:bg-gray-900">
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-full bg-blue-100 pl-3 pr-1 py-1 text-sm font-medium text-blue-700 dark:bg-blue-900 dark:text-blue-300">
        Removable
        <button class="ml-1 flex h-4 w-4 items-center justify-center rounded-full hover:bg-blue-200 dark:hover:bg-blue-700">
          <svg class="h-3 w-3" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>
        </button>
      </span>
    </div>

    <h3>Interactive</h3>
    <p>Set <code>interactive</code> to make the chip clickable, useful for filter chips that toggle on/off.</p>

    <CodeBlock title="chip-features.tsx" code={`import { Chip } from '@storyhouse/components';

export function ChipFeatures() {
  return (
    <div className="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
      <Chip variant="success" dot>Online</Chip>
      <Chip variant="primary" dot>Away</Chip>
      <Chip variant="danger" dot>Offline</Chip>
      <Chip variant="primary" removable>Tag One</Chip>
      <Chip variant="primary" removable>Tag Two</Chip>
      <Chip variant="default" interactive onClick={() => alert('Clicked!')}>
        Click me
      </Chip>
    </div>
  );
}`} />
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="props">Props</h2>
    <PropsTable
      rows={[
        { name: 'variant', type: '"default" | "primary" | "success" | "warning" | "danger" | "outline"', default: '"default"', description: 'Visual variant for the chip.' },
        { name: 'size', type: '"sm" | "md"', default: '"md"', description: 'Controls padding and font size.' },
        { name: 'icon', type: 'ReactNode', default: '-', description: 'Icon displayed before the label.' },
        { name: 'dot', type: 'boolean', default: 'false', description: 'Shows a colored dot before the label.' },
        { name: 'removable', type: 'boolean', default: 'false', description: 'Shows a remove (X) button.' },
        { name: 'onRemove', type: '(e: React.MouseEvent) => void', default: '-', description: 'Callback fired when the remove button is clicked.' },
        { name: 'interactive', type: 'boolean', default: 'false', description: 'Makes the chip clickable with hover styles.' },
        { name: 'onClick', type: '(e: React.MouseEvent) => void', default: '-', description: 'Callback fired when the chip is clicked (interactive only).' },
        { name: 'children', type: 'ReactNode', default: '-', description: 'Content of the chip.' },
        { name: 'className', type: 'string', default: '-', description: 'Additional CSS classes merged via tailwind-merge.' },
      ]}
    />
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="edge-cases">Edge Cases &amp; Best Practices</h2>

    <h3>Long Labels</h3>
    <p>Chip does not truncate labels by default. For long text, the chip expands horizontally. Keep labels under 20 characters for best results.</p>

    <h3>Remove + Interactive</h3>
    <p>When both <code>removable</code> and <code>interactive</code> are set, the remove button click stops propagation so it doesn't trigger the parent <code>onClick</code>.</p>

    <h3>Stacking Chips</h3>
    <p>When displaying many chips, wrap them in a <code>flex flex-wrap gap-2</code> container. Chips naturally wrap to the next line.</p>

    <h3>Icon + Dot</h3>
    <p>Both <code>icon</code> and <code>dot</code> can be used together. The dot renders before the icon, and the icon renders before the label.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="implementation">Implementation Details</h2>
    <p>
      Chips use <code>class-variance-authority</code> (CVA) for variant and size management.
      The remove button uses <code>e.stopPropagation()</code> to prevent triggering the parent
      <code>onClick</code>. All colors include <code>dark:</code> variants for automatic dark mode.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="accessibility">Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Remove button has <code>aria-label="Remove"</code></li>
      <li>Interactive chips render as <code>button</code> elements with proper keyboard support</li>
      <li>Dot indicator includes <code>aria-hidden="true"</code></li>
      <li>Icon elements use <code>aria-hidden="true"</code></li>
      <li>Focus-visible ring on interactive and removable chips</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="storybook-preview">Interactive Preview</h2>
    <StorybookPreview id="components-chip--default" title="Chip — Storybook" height="500" />
  </section>
</DocLayout>
